Style Guide for CPSC 334 Final Project

Naming Conventions
Use meaningful names
Classes: PascalCase
Functions/Methods: snake_case
Variables: snake_case

Indentation
Done with a single tab

Structure
Define classes at the top, and `main()` at the bottom

Comments
Use comments sparingly, only when code is not self-explanatory, put a comment before each function and each test, can be as simple as needed to describe its function

Error Handling
Use try-except blocks in main code to handle user input errors, and arise a `ValueError` for invalid inputs

Testing
Done with pytest
Use descriptive test function names that explain what is being tested

Organization
Keep functions short and focused on a single task
Avoid complex logic in the main function; delegate to functions

Imports
Import modules at the top of the file